**Smart Enumerations in DDD C# Application**

Smart enumerations are a way to implement enumerations in a more robust and maintainable way. They provide additional functionality beyond the basic enumeration values.

Here's an example implementation of a smart enumeration in C#:

```csharp
public enum Color
{
    [Description("Red")]
    Red,
    [Description("Green")]
    Green,
    [Description("Blue")]
    Blue
}

public static class ColorExtensions
{
    public static string GetDescription(this Color color)
    {
        var fieldInfo = color.GetType().GetField(color.ToString());
        var descriptionAttribute = (DescriptionAttribute)fieldInfo.GetCustomAttributes(typeof(DescriptionAttribute), false).FirstOrDefault();

        return descriptionAttribute != null ? descriptionAttribute.Description : color.ToString();
    }

    public static string ToFriendlyString(this Color color)
    {
        return color.GetDescription().ToLower();
    }
}
```

